simple economy (part of the TODO for population)
	each region has a given population; part of it supports the city; the others can be ordered to collect resources
	wood, stone, iron and gold require special buildings to be produced
	there are buildings that allow producing resources more efficiently (e.g. irrigation)
	gold comes from taxes; the population that is not busy collecting resources does not require payment (and results in gold income)
	from the free population one can set the proportion that will collect each of the resources (food, stone, wood, iron); the income is not proportional to the number of people
	food cannot be stocked indefinitely (it rots)
	each controlled region requires gold to be governed and each building requires more gold; as a result regions with low population can cost gold

? windmill
	+1 food
? watermill
	+1 food
? tillage
	food +2
drift mine (requires: mine)
	stone +2
gold mine (requires mine)
	+1 gold
foundry

region-specific characteristics
	wood (required for sawmill)
	ore (required for mine)
	gold (required for gold mine)
	climate (determines production of food and wood; determines water availability)
		water is require for watermill, irrigation, moat, etc.

technologies:
    conservatory
	tillage; crop rotation
    drainage / sewage
	academy / university

trading
	constructions involved: marketplace, roads, port
	trading benefits are determined by population of the region and its neighbors
	roads increase the benefits from land neighbors
	port increases the benefits from sea neighbors (? whatever that means)

